INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1403','letter','1785-06-16','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Patrick','Henry','','individual','','In a letter of January the 12th, to Governor Harrison, I informed him of the necessity that the statuary should see General Washington; that we should accordingly send him over unless the Executive disapproved of it','ltr_thj1403.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1404','letter','1785-06-17','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Monroe','','individual','','I am much pleased with Otto\'s appointment; he is good-humored, affectionate to America, will see things in a friendly light when they admit of it, in a rational one always, and will not pique himself on writing every trifling circumstance of irritation to his court.','ltr_thj1404.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1405','letter','1785-06-21','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Charles','Thomson','','individual','','The political world is almost lulled to sleep by the lethargic state of the Dutch negotiation, which will probably end in peace.','ltr_thj1405.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1406','letter','1785-06-22','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','William','Carmichael','','individual','','Our latest letters from America are of the middle of April, and are extremely barren of news. Congress had not yet proposed a time for their recess, though it was thought a recess would take place.','ltr_thj1406.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1407','letter','1785-06-23','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Adams','','individual','','What is become of this Mr. Lambe? I am uneasy at the delay of that business, since we know the ultimate decision of Congress.','ltr_thj1407.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1408','letter','1785-07-05','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Monroe','','individual','','Little has occurred since my last. Peace seems to show herself under a more decided form. The Emperor is now on a journey to Italy, and the two Dutch Plenipotentiaries have set out for Vienna','ltr_thj1408.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1409','letter','1785-07-05','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Sprowle','','individual','','I wish you may be rightly informed that the property of Mr. Sprowle is yet unsold. It was advertised so long ago, as to found a presumption that the sale has taken place. In any event, you may safely go to Virginia.','ltr_thj1409.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1410','letter','1785-07-07','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Adams','','individual','','We daily expect from the Baron Thulemeyer the French column for our treaty with his sovereign.','ltr_thj1410.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1411','letter','1785-07-10','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','George','Washington','','individual','','Mr. Houdon would much sooner have had the honor of attending you, but for a spell of sickness, which long induced us to despair of his recovery, and from which he is but recently recovered.','ltr_thj1411.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1412','letter','1785-07-11','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Patrick','Henry','','individual','','Mr. Houdon\'s long and desperate illness has retarded, till now, his departure for Virginia. We had hoped, from our first conversations with him, that it would be easy to make our terms, and that the cost of the statue and expense of sending him, would be but about a thousand guineas.','ltr_thj1412.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1413','letter','1785-07-12','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Richard','Lee','','individual','','You are right in supposing all letters opened which come either through the French or English channel, unless trusted to a passenger. Yours had evidently been opened, and I think I never received one through the post office which had not been.','ltr_thj1413.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1414','letter','1785-07-12','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','','','group','Virginia Delegates in Congress','In consequence of the orders of the legislative and executive bodies of Virginia, I have engaged Monsieur Houdon to make the statue of General General Washington. For this purpose it is necessary for him to see the General.','ltr_thj1414.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1415','letter','1785-07-12','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Jay','','individual','','While Captain Jones was hovering on the coast of England, in the year 1779, a British pilot, John Jackson by name, came on board him, supposing him to be British. Captain Jones found it convenient to detain him as a pilot','ltr_thj1415.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1416','letter','1785-07-13','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Briet','','individual','','I am glad to hear that the Council have ordered restitution of the merchandise seized at L\'Orient, contrary to the freedom of the place.','ltr_thj1416.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1417','letter','1785-07-13','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','','','individual','','I am very sensible that no trade can be on a more desperate footing than that of tobacco, in this country; and that our merchants must abandon the French markets, if they are not permitted to sell the productions they bring','ltr_thj1417.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1418','letter','1785-07-17','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Stiles','','individual','','But why, you will ask, do I send you old almanacs, which are proverbially useless? Because, in these publications have appeared, from time to time, some of the most precious things in astronomy.','ltr_thj1418.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1419','letter','1785-07-28','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Adams','','individual','','Mr. Short sets out immediately. I have put into his hands a letter of instructions how to conduct himself, which I have signed, leaving a space above for your signature.','ltr_thj1419.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1420','letter','1785-07-29','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Hogendorp','','individual','','Congress, having made a very considerable purchase of land from the Indians, have established a land office, and settled the mode of selling the lands. Their plan is judicious.','ltr_thj1420.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1421','letter','1785-07-30','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Staphorst','','individual','','Supposing that the funds, which are the object of your inquiry, are those which constitute what we call our domestic debt, it is my opinion that they are absolutely secure: I have no doubt at all but that they will be paid','ltr_thj1421.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1422','letter','1785-07-31','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Adams','','individual','','When the first article of our instructions of May 7th, 1784, was under debate in Congress, it was proposed that neither party should make the other pay, in their ports, greater duties, than they paid in the ports of the other.','ltr_thj1422.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1423','letter','1785-08-03','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','De Castries','','individual','','The enclosed copy of a letter from Captain John Paul Jones, on the subject on which your Excellency did me the honor to write me, on the day of July, will inform you that there is still occasion to be troublesome to you.','ltr_thj1423.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1424','letter','1785-08-03','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John Paul','Jones','','individual','','Will you be so good as to make an inquiry into all the circumstances relative to Peyrouse\'s expedition, which seem to ascertain his destination.','ltr_thj1424.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1425','letter','1785-08-06','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Adams','','individual','','I now enclose you a draught of a treaty for the Barbary States, together with the notes Benjamin Franklin left me.','ltr_thj1425.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1426','letter','1785-08-07','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Price','','individual','','The concern you therein express as to the effect of your pamphlet in America, induces me to trouble you with some observations on that subject.','ltr_thj1426.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1427','letter','1785-08-10','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Adams','','individual','','The cause of the balance against this country in favor of England, as well as its amount, is not agreed on. No doubt, the rage for English manufactures must be a principal cause.','ltr_thj1427.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1428','letter','1785-08-10','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Sprowle','','individual','','In your letter of June the 21st, you asked my opinion whether yourself or your son might venture to go to Virginia, to claim your possessions there?','ltr_thj1428.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1429','letter','1785-08-13','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John Paul','Jones','','individual','','I write by Mr. Cairnes merely to inform you, that I have, as yet, received no answer from the Marechal de Castries. I am in daily expectation of one.','ltr_thj1429.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1430','letter','1785-08-13','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Buchanan','','individual','','I wrote to you, acknowledging the receipt, and apprizing you, that between that date and the 1st of August, it would be impossible to procure, and get to your hands, the drafts you desired.','ltr_thj1430.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1431','letter','1785-08-14','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Jay','','individual','','I took an opportunity of asking the Count de Vergennes, whether the Chevalier Luzerne proposed to return to America. He answered me that he did; and that he was here, for a time only, to arrange his private affairs.','ltr_thj1431.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1432','letter','1785-08-15','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','De Vergennes','','individual','','In the conversation which I had the honor of having with your Excellency, a few days ago, on the importance of placing, at this time, the commerce between France and America on the best footing possible','ltr_thj1432.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1433','letter','1785-08-17','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John Paul','Jones','','individual','','he has not been able to get an authentic roll of the crew of the Alliance, and that, in the probable case of there having been some French subjects among them, it will be just that you should give security to repay their portions.','ltr_thj1433.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1434','letter','1785-08-18','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','William','Carmichael','','individual','','I see with extreme satisfaction and gratitude, the friendly interposition of the court of Spain with the Emperor of Morocco, on the subject of the brig Betsy, and I am persuaded it will produce the happiest effects in America. ','ltr_thj1434.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1435','letter','1785-08-19','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Peter','Carr','','individual','','Time now begins to be precious to you. Every day you lose, will retard a day your entrance on that public stage whereon you may begin to be useful to yourself. However, the way to repair the loss is to improve the future time.','ltr_thj1435.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1436','letter','1785-08-20','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Page','','individual','','This correspondence is grateful to some of my warmest feelings, as the friendships of my youth are those which adhere closest to me, and in which I most confide. My principal happiness is now in the retrospect of life.','ltr_thj1436.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1437','letter','1785-08-23','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Jay','','individual','','I shall sometimes ask your permission to write you letters, not official, but private. The present is of this kind, and is occasioned by the question proposed in yours of June the 14th; \'Whether it would be useful to us, to carry all our own productions, or none?\'','ltr_thj1437.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1438','letter','1785-08-28','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Monroe','','individual','','Every thing looks like peace here. The settlement between the Emperor and Dutch is not yet published, but it is believed to be agreed on.','ltr_thj1438.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1439','letter','1785-08-29','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John Paul','Jones','','individual','','I pray you to furnish me with all the evidence you can, as to what French subjects may be entitled to any part of the monies you will receive, and to how much, each of them','ltr_thj1439.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1440','letter','1785-08-30','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Jay','','individual','','I enclose you a correspondence which has taken place between the Marechal de Castries, minister of the Marine, and myself. It is on the subject of the prize-money, due to the officers and crew of the Alliance','ltr_thj1440.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1441','letter','1785-09-01','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','James','Madison','','individual','','All is quiet here. The Emperor and Dutch have certainly agreed, though they have not published their agreement. Most of his schemes in Germany must be postponed, if they are not prevented by the confederacy of many of the Germanic body','ltr_thj1441.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1442','letter','1785-09-01','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Dumas','','individual','','On a review of our letters to the Baron de Thulemeyer, I do not find that we had proposed that the treaty should be in two columns, the one English, and the other what he should think proper.','ltr_thj1442.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1443','letter','1785-09-04','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Adams','','individual','','Supposing that we should begin with the Emperor of Morocco, a letter to the Emperor and instructions to Mr. Barclay, seemed necessary. I have therefore sketched such outlines for these, as appear to me to be proper.','ltr_thj1443.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1444','letter','1785-09-00','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','','','individual','','That the United States of America, heretofore connected in government with Great Britain, had found it necessary for their happiness to separate from her, and to assume an independent station.','ltr_thj1444.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1445','letter','1785-09-05','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','David','Hartley','','individual','','With respect to America, I will rather give you a general view of its situation, than merely relate recent events.','ltr_thj1445.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1446','letter','1785-09-06','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Geismer','','individual','','You are now too distant from America, to be much interested in what passes there. From the London gazettes, and the papers copying them, you are led to suppose that all there is anarchy, discontent, and civil war.','ltr_thj1446.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1447','letter','1785-09-11','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Langdon','','individual','','Your Captain Yeaton being here, furnishes me an opportunity of paying the tribute of my congratulations on your appointment to the government of your State, which I do sincerely.','ltr_thj1447.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1448','letter','1785-09-14','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Lister','Asquith','','individual','','Several of your letters have been received, and we have been occupied in endeavors to have you discharged: but these have been ineffectual. If our information be right, you are mistaken in supposing you are already condemned.','ltr_thj1448.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1449','letter','1785-09-19','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Adams','','individual','','Lambe has arrived. He brings new full powers to us from Congress, to appoint persons to negotiate with the Barbary States; but we are to sign the treaties.','ltr_thj1449.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1450','letter','1785-09-20','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','James','Madison','','individual','','I received this summer a letter from Messrs. Buchanan and Hay, as Directors of the public buildings desiring I would have drawn for them plans of sundry buildings, and, in the first place, of a capital.','ltr_thj1450.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1451','letter','1785-09-20','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Edmund','Randolph','','individual','','Being in your debt for ten volumes of Buffon, I have endeavored to find something that would be agreeable to you to receive, in return.','ltr_thj1451.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1452','letter','1785-09-24','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Adams','','individual','','The sentiments you therein expressed, were such as were entertained in America till the commercial proclamation, and such as would again return, were a rational conduct to be adopted by Great Britain.','ltr_thj1452.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1453','letter','1785-09-24','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Adams','','individual','','I transmit you herewith, copies of the papers he brought to us on the subject of the Barbary treaties. You will see by them, that Congress have adopted the very plan which we were proposing to pursue.','ltr_thj1453.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1454','letter','1785-09-25','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','F','Hopkinson','','individual','','I do not altogether despair of making something of your method of quilling, though, as yet, the prospect is not favorable. I applaud much your perseverance in improving this instrument','ltr_thj1454.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1455','letter','1785-09-26','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Lister','Asquith','','individual','','I now wait for the letter from your lawyer, as, till I know the real nature and state of your process, it is impossible for me to judge what can be done for you here.','ltr_thj1455.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1456','letter','1785-09-26','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','R','Izard','','individual','','I received, a few days ago, your favor of the 10th of June, and am to thank you for the trouble you have given yourself, to procure me information on the subject of the commerce of your State.','ltr_thj1456.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1457','letter','1785-09-29','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Richard','OBryan','','individual','','I have received your letter, and shall exert myself for you. Be assured of hearing from me soon','ltr_thj1457.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1458','letter','1785-09-30','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Bellini','','individual','','The truth of Voltaire\'s observation offers itself perpetually, that every man here must be either the hammer or the anvil. ','ltr_thj1458.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1459','letter','1785-10-02','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','James','Madison','','individual','','You therein speak of a new method of raising water by steam, which you suppose will come into general use. I know of no new method of that kind','ltr_thj1459.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1460','letter','1785-10-05','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Benjamin','Franklin','','individual','','We have no public news worth communicating to you, but the signing of preliminaries between the Emperor and Dutch. The question is, then, with whom the Emperor will pick the next quarrel.','ltr_thj1460.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1461','letter','1785-10-05','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Samuel','Osgood','','individual','','It was with very sincere pleasure I heard of your appointment to the board of treasury, as well from the hope that it might not be disagreeable to yourself, as from the confidence that your administration would be wise.','ltr_thj1461.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1462','letter','1785-10-06','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Jay','','individual','','The Emperor and Dutch have signed preliminaries, which are now made public. You will see them in the papers which accompany this. They still leave a good deal to discussion.','ltr_thj1462.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1463','letter','1785-10-11','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Elbridge','Gerry','','individual','','I received, last night, the letter signed by yourself and the other gentlemen, delegates of Massachusetts and Virginia, recommending Mr. Sayre for the Barbary negotiations.','ltr_thj1463.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1464','letter','1785-10-11','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','de Vergennes','','individual','','I have the honor of enclosing to your Excellency, a report of the voyage of an American ship, the first which has gone to China.','ltr_thj1464.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1466','letter','1785-10-12','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Staphorst','','individual','','With respect to the expediency of the arrangement you propose to make with Mr. Parker, I must observe to you, that it would be altogether out of my province to give an official opinion, for your direction.','ltr_thj1466.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1467','letter','1785-10-12','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Desbordes','','individual','','There are, in the prison of St. Pol de Léon, six or seven citizens of the United States of America, charged with having attempted a contraband of tobacco, but, as they say themselves, forced into that port by stress of weather.','ltr_thj1467.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1468','letter','1785-10-13','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Hogendorp','','individual','','The British government, as you may naturally suppose, have it much at heart to reconcile their nation to the loss of America. This is essential to the repose, perhaps even to the safety of the King and his ministers.','ltr_thj1468.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1469','letter','1785-10-15','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','J','Bannister','','individual','','I should sooner have answered the paragraph in your letter, of September the 19th, respecting the best seminary for the education of youth, in Europe, but that it was necessary for me to make inquiries on the subject.','ltr_thj1469.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1470','letter','1785-10-18','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','William','Carmichael','','individual','','the constant expectation of the departure of the persons whom I formerly gave you reason to expect, has prevented my writing, as it has done yours.','ltr_thj1470.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1471','letter','1785-10-25','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Van Staphorst','','individual','','In order to give you the information you desire, on the subject of the liquidated debts of the United States, and the comparative footing on which they stand, I must observe to you, that the first and great division of our federal debt, is...','ltr_thj1471.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1472','letter','1785-11-04','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','William','Carmichael','','individual','','At length a confidential opportunity arrives for conveying to you a cipher; it will be handed you by the bearer, Mr, Lambe. Copies of it are in the hands of Mr. Adams, at London','ltr_thj1472.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1473','letter','1785-11-04','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Richard','OBryan','','individual','','Mr. Adams, the American minister at London, and myself, have agreed to authorize the bearer hereof, Mr. Lambe, to treat for your redemption, and that of your companions taken in American vessels','ltr_thj1473.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1474','letter','1785-11-12','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','W','Seward','','individual','','The freedom of commerce between Ireland and America is undoubtedly very interesting to both countries. If fair play be given to the natural advantages of Ireland, she must come in for a distinguished share of that commerce.','ltr_thj1474.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1475','letter','1785-11-14','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','de Vergennes','','individual','','I take the liberty of troubling your Excellency on behalf of six citizens of the United States, who have been for some time confined in the prison of St. Pol de Léon, and of referring for particulars to the enclosed state of their case. Some of the material facts ther','ltr_thj1475.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1476','letter','1785-11-19','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Adams','','individual','','This has led to discussions with the ministers, which give us a hope that we may get the duties taken off in perpetuum. This done, a most abundant market for our oil will be opened by this country','ltr_thj1476.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1477','letter','1785-11-20','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','de Vergennes','','individual','','I am equally persuaded they will pay the most serious attention to that part of your Excellency\'s letter, which mentions the information you have received of certain acts or regulations of navigation and commerce, passed in some of the United States','ltr_thj1477.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1478','letter','1785-11-23','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Lister','Asquith','','individual','','I have sent to the Count de Vergennes a statement of your case, of which the enclosed is a copy. I wish you would read it over, and if there be any fact stated in it, which is wrong, let me know it','ltr_thj1478.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1479','letter','1785-11-27','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Adams','','individual','','I sincerely rejoice that Portugal is stepping forward in the business of treaty, and that there is a probability that we may at length do something under our commissions, which may produce a solid benefit to our constituents.','ltr_thj1479.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1480','letter','1785-12-04','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','David','Humphreys','','individual','','I enclose you a letter from Gatteaux, observing that there will be an anachronism, if, in making a medal to commemorate the victory of Saratoga, he puts on General Gates the insignia of the Cincinnati, which did not exist at that date.','ltr_thj1480.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1481','letter','1785-12-10','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Adams','','individual','','On the arrival of Mr. Boylston, I carried him to the Marquis De La Fayette, who received from him communications of his object. This was to get a remission of the duties on his cargo of oil','ltr_thj1481.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1482','letter','1785-12-11','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Adams','','individual','','You know the immense amount of Beaumarchais\' accounts with the United States, and that Mr. Barclay was authorized to settle them. Beaumarchais had pertinaciously insisted on settling them with Congress.','ltr_thj1482.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1483','letter','1785-12-21','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','de Vergennes','','individual','','It is on the case of Asquith and others, citizens of the United States, in whose behalf I had taken the liberty of asking your interference.','ltr_thj1483.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1484','letter','1785-12-22','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','','','position','Governor of Georgia','The death of the late General Oglethorpe, who had considerable possessions in Georgia, has given rise, as we understand, to questions whether these possessions have become the property of the State, or have been transferred by his will to his widow','ltr_thj1484.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1485','letter','1785-12-22','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','','','group','','you will perceive that the claims of the Chevalier de Mezieres, nephew to the late General Oglethorpe, to his possessions within your State, have attracted the attention of the ministry here','ltr_thj1485.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1486','letter','1785-12-27','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Adams','','individual','','You have been consulted in the case of the Chevalier de Mezieres, nephew to General Oglethorpe, and are understood to have given an opinion derogatory of our treaty with France.','ltr_thj1486.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1487','letter','1786-01-02','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Jay','','individual','','Several conferences and letters having passed between the Count de Vergennes and myself, on the subject of the commerce of this country with the United States, I think them sufficiently interesting to be communicated to Congress.','ltr_thj1487.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1488','letter','1786-01-03','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','T','Hopkinson','','individual','','He showed me his first invention; the price of the machine was twenty-five guineas: then his second, which he had been able to make for about half that sum. Both of these had a mainspring and a balance-wheel, for their mover and regulator.','ltr_thj1488.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1489','letter','1786-01-04','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','George','Washington','','individual','','have been honored with your letter of September the 26th, which was delivered me by Mr. Houdon, who is safely returned. He has brought with him the mould of the face only, having left the other parts of his work with his workmen to come by some other conveyance.','ltr_thj1489.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1490','letter','1786-01-07','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','A','Cary','','individual','','The very few of my countrymen who happen to be punctual, will find their punctuality a misfortune to them. Of this I shall give you a proof by the present application, which I should not make to you, if I did not know you to be superior to the torpidity of our climate.','ltr_thj1490.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1491','letter','1786-01-12','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Nathanael','Greene','','individual','','I immediately made inquiries on the subject of the frigate you had authorized your relation to sell to this government, and I found that he had long before that sold her to government, and sold her very well, as I understood.','ltr_thj1491.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1492','letter','1786-01-13','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Lister','Asquith','','individual','','The reason I have not written to you for some time, has been the constant expectation of receiving an order for your discharge. I have not received it however.','ltr_thj1492.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1493','letter','1786-01-26','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','Buchanan','','individual','','I had the honor of writing to you on the receipt of your orders to procure draughts for the public buildings, and again on the 13th of August. In the execution of these orders, two methods of proceeding presented themselves to my mind.','ltr_thj1493.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1494','letter','1786-02-07','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Adams','','individual','','I was perfectly satisfied before I received your letter, that your opinion had been misunderstood or misrepresented in the case of the Chevalier de Mezieres.','ltr_thj1494.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1495','letter','1786-02-08','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','James','Madison','','individual','','I have purchased little for you in the book way since I sent the catalogue of my former purchases. I wish, first, to have your answer to that, and your information, what parts of these purchases went out of your plan.','ltr_thj1495.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1496','letter','1786-02-09','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','The Mr. John Ledyard, who proposes to undertake the journey through the northern parts of Asia and America, is a citizen of Connecticut, one of the United States of America.','ltr_thj1496.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1497','letter','1786-02-20','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','Hilliard','d Auberteuil','','individual','','America cannot but be flattered with the choice of the subject, on which you are at present employing your pen. The memory of the American Revolution will be immortal, and will immortalize those who record it.','ltr_thj1497.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1498','letter','1786-02-28','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','De Vergennes','','individual','','Circumstances of public duty calling me suddenly to London, I take the liberty of mentioning it to your Excellency, and of asking a few minutes audience of you, at as early a day and hour as will be convenient to you','ltr_thj1498.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1499','letter','1786-03-08','Paris','','FRA','Thomas','Jefferson','','','De Reyneval','','individual','','His Excellency, Count de Vergennes, having been pleased to say that he would give orders at Calais, for the admission of certain articles which I wish to bring with me from England, I have thought it best to give a description of them, before my departure.','ltr_thj1499.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1500','letter','1786-03-12','London','','ENG','Thomas','Jefferson','','John','Jay','','individual','','The date of a letter from London will doubtless be as unexpected to you as it was unforeseen by myself, a few days ago.','ltr_thj1500.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thj1501','letter','1786-03-08','London','','ENG','Thomas','Jefferson','','David','Humphreys','','individual','','It is with sincere concern that I meet this event, as it deprives me not only of your aid in the office in which we have been joined, but also of your society, which has been to me a source of the greatest satisfaction.','ltr_thj1501.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Project Gutenberg EBook of Memoir, Correspondence, And Miscellanies, From The Papers Of Thomas Jefferson, by Thomas Jefferson');
